body:
@mrry to recommend on cmake. What I see as the error is this:

```
CMake Error at tf_python.cmake:612 (add_executable):
00:01:01.735   Error evaluating generator expression:
00:01:01.735 
00:01:01.735     $<TARGET_OBJECTS:tf_contrib_periodic_resample_op>
00:01:01.735 
00:01:01.735   Objects of target "tf_contrib_periodic_resample_op" referenced but no such
00:01:01.735   target exists.
00:01:01.735 Call Stack (most recent call first):
00:01:01.735   tf_python.cmake:703 (GENERATE_PYTHON_OP_LIB)
00:01:01.735   CMakeLists.txt:288 (include)
```

If you exclude it your contribution from cmake, it will be excluded from windows. This may make future attempts to move this into core difficult. But if this is just meant to be excluded in windows builds you can revert all changes to the current cmake files, and add the exclusion of your test files to tf_tests.cmake.
